name: UberX
internal_notes: The most common and budget-friendly ride option. Great for individuals or small groups.

name: Uber Black
description: Premium rides with professional drivers in high-end vehicles.
internal_notes: Luxury product tier with stricter vehicle and driver requirements.

name: UberXL
description: Spacious rides for groups up to 6 people.
internal_notes: Ideal for families or groups with luggage. Costs more than UberX.

name: Uber Share
description: Share your ride and save money.
internal_notes: Carpooling-style rides. Users share their ride with others headed in the same direction to reduce cost.

name: Wait and Save
description: Flexible pickup times for lower fares.
internal_notes: Riders who aren’t in a hurry can opt to wait longer and pay less for their trip.

name: Uber Pet
description: Bring your pet along for the ride with pet-friendly drivers.
internal_notes: Designed for riders traveling with pets — drivers opt in to this product type.

name: Uber Assist
description: Rides with trained drivers who can assist passengers with mobility needs or special assistance.
internal_notes: Specialized service for seniors, disabled riders, or anyone needing assistance entering/exiting vehicles.

name: Uber Autonomous
description: Ride in an electric autonomous vehicle powered by AI.
internal_notes: Autonomous vehicle product, electric-powered. May be experimental or limited release.

name: 2-Wheels
description: Bike or Scooter to quickly get around the city.
internal_notes: Can be bike, scooter, motorcycle or similar small personal vehicles.

name: Uber Teens
description: A safe and supervised way for teens to ride with Uber.
internal_notes: Parents can set up supervised accounts for teens aged 13–17. Features include trip tracking, safety alerts, and contact controls.
